    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-12T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-12T23:00:00-05:00" n="357"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/739: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-13T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 13, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received September 13—7
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>693. During a visit from Japanese Consul General this morning he informed me he
                    had learned of proposals to evacuate Americans from Hankow by Canton–Hankow
                    Railway, that the Japanese Navy does not wish to give any appearance of blocking
                    egress of foreigners from interior and are agreeable to proposal, and that if
                    proposal is carried out he hopes we will give him advance notice so that
                    Japanese naval authorities can be informed. He added, however, that it is the
                    hope that if this route is to be followed the evacuation will be carried out as
                    soon as possible as the railway is known to be moving Chinese troops and
                    military supplies.</p>
                <p>Sent to Nanking, repeated to the Department and Hankow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
